## Overview

This is a **list** data source: it returns every tag the instance defines,
optionally narrowed by a name substring. It takes no primary key and always
returns a (possibly empty) list — it never errors on zero matches.

To fetch exactly one tag (by `id` or exact `name`), use the singular
[`mistershell_tag`](tag.md) data source instead; that one resolves to a single
tag and errors if the lookup is ambiguous or empty.

## Argument

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `search` | Optional. Case-insensitive **substring** match against the tag name. Returns only tags whose name contains this value. **Omit it to return all tags.** |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Synthetic constant (`tags`); this is a list data source with no primary key. |
| `tags` | List of matching tags. Each element is an object with the fields below. |

Each element of `tags` has:

| field | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Tag ID (`int64`). |
| `name` | Tag name. |
| `color` | Tag color. A free-form string (1-16 characters); there is no fixed palette or enum (see the [`mistershell_tag`](tag.md) page). |
| `description` | Tag description (may be null). |
| `resource_count` | Number of network resources currently assigned this tag. |
